If I get a high score, I should be able to win a nice prize... But I only had a little salad for lunch — the bowstring feels so heavy...
When Mondstadt was first founded, archery was a basic skill. People hunted in order to survive.
Ha, are you sure this is a challenge? That balloon is so huge! Why don't we... compete to see who can shoot the stem off an apple and have it drop to the ground without blemish?

Jean is very serious about the meaning passed down through this game, so I guess I shouldn't take it too lightly. Let's shoot a few Bouquet Balloons down, and then we can go back and make afternoon tea.
It takes a long period of training to become a battle-ready archer. These games are only enough to pass the time.

Ugh, this bow is soooo hard to use, I just don't have the strength... But if I tied a mini-Jumpy Dumpty to the back of the arrow to make it fly, it should go waaaaay further, right? It could even blow all those balloons up!

I still need to conduct more research and undertake more training before I can use a bow, and even then, I think that my skills can only come into play in this game. My bone specimens are all collected... and I don't usually get the opportunity, or feel the need to go hunting...
Flying... long metal branch. Very strong. But claws, stronger.

Fischl: "O sorcerous bolt of sacred judgment, hear one's will and surge forth! Render as dust all falsehoods within your sight!"\nOz: "Splendid shooting, mein Fräulein! But is it really proper for me to support you from the side in this manner?"

Familiarizing myself with the weapons that other adventurers use allows me to better myself, and it is also my duty as an adventure team leader! My current score is nothing to brag about... I have to give it all I've got!
Might have missed a few balloons back there... but it's about having fun, not about seeing who scores higher or lower!
Why, if you asked me to set the rules, I'd have everyone run and shoot at the same time! I mean, that's what it's like when we go hunting!
Oh dear, is this what they call a height advantage? I suppose I can go a little easy on you all to make things a bit more exciting.

Fischl: "Behold, the sight of the Prinzessin der Verurteilung as she descends from the darkling heavens amid the profuse flowering of ideals — how like it is unto the descent of a savior of the mortal realms!"\nOz: "If I may impose, mein Fräulein, please refrain from grabbing my wings to perform tight turns. I fear that my feathers might fall off..."
As the Gliding Champion of Mondstadt, nothing but a high score will do for this challenge! Still, you've really improved at a frightening rate, Honorary Knight!
I have to practice my gliding skills even while I try to get a high score. That way, I should be able to glide my way to usually impassable areas to collect research samples...
Jumping down looks so fun! I want to play some more! But, uh... could I leave my pack and Dodoco with you, Honorary Knight?
Just collecting flower balls and garlands won't be quite enough to capture the true joys of flying! Maybe feeding some birds in mid-air would feel even freer?
My stomach's a little... heavy, but I'll try to make up for it. Gliding is a necessary skill for a knight, after all!
The winds that blow from all sides have the scent of new sprouts and buds, bringing finches and crystalflies that surround me. Ah... this really is a ritual filled with life.
The techniques used during this game can also be used in battle. I find it most meaningful. Getting a high score would be most praiseworthy, too.
Hmm, I've got it! Maybe I'll take the stage on a glider next time! I wonder if that'll add some freshness to the performance...
My tail stabilizes me as I fall, so no wind glider, no worries! It's just... it's just that my hands are too short, and I miss the flower balls sometimes... Urgh.
Hmm, the distribution of these flower crowns... I wonder if they'll produce good results if I combined them with hydromancy? Hmm, is this what they call the revelation of the wind?
Um... I'm not very good at playing songs and stuff. Can anyone teach me? Please! I'll trade some of my treasures with you!
Playing music for everyone to create a comfy atmosphere is one of a maid's duties. I will do my best.
The techniques of playing the lyre are a bard's secret. If we were to combine it all into a textbook, we could probably create a new field of study altogether!
Music... very nice. But... don't understand.
Soothing music really helps me relax... Now, if a certain cutie would volunteer to be my private musician and play me a lullaby, that would be even better.
I do know how to play music. Is it so strange?
If I learn a few awesome tunes, will it help raise my teammates' spirits? Well, it might at least bring a smile to their faces when we're down on our luck!
What an interesting diversion. Since everyone's in high spirits, it would truly be a shame if I didn't pitch in a little!
Singing and playing are skills any idol must have! Once I've gotten used to this lyre, I'll only get better and better!
Music and astrology share some similarities. As such, understanding its principles is nothing short of elementary. I just need a bit of time to familiarize myself with this instrument...

Poetry and music are both much-beloved by the citizens of Mondstadt, and the Knights, naturally, share this enjoyment. As the Acting Grand Master, I sometimes represent us at celebrations, so I do know a few rudimentary tunes.
I've never practiced any instruments, but I've sometimes heard the distant sounds of the lyre while sketching outdoors. I suppose I could try to play a tune from memory and intuition.
